<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:my="http://example.com/my" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_fændon" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>fændon</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>желание</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>wish</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>желанный</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>desired</q></cit></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fændonæj</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>по желанию</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>optional</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>добровольно</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>voluntarily</q></cit></sense></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>barvændonæj</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>добровольно</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>voluntarily</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note></sense></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_fændon." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>fændon xorz kæm ī!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>где (найдешь) хорошее (по желанию!)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>where will you find good (%boptional%b)!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>kæd nin æj radta fændonæj — xwæzdær; ku niffærsmæ wa — æxecæn fuddær</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>если он отдаст нам ее (дочь) добровольно — тем лучше; если заупрямится — тем хуже для него</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>if he gives us his daughter voluntarily, so much the better; if he is stubborn, so much the worse for him</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>59%l192–193%l</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>xwarz æxsævæ in bafændon kænuj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>желает ему доброй ночи</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he wishes him good night</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>ævændonæj æj lævardtoncæ lægmæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>против желания выдавали ее замуж</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>she was married against her desire</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>I 55</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>fændon xorz kæm ī!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>где (найдешь) хорошее (по желанию!)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>where will you find good (%boptional%b)!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>kæd nin æj radta fændonæj — xwæzdær; ku niffærsmæ wa — æxecæn fuddær</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>если он отдаст нам ее (дочь) добровольно — тем лучше; если заупрямится — тем хуже для него</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>if he gives us his daughter voluntarily, so much the better; if he is stubborn, so much the worse for him</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>59%l192–193%l</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>xwarz æxsævæ in bafændon kænuj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>желает ему доброй ночи</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he wishes him good night</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>ævændonæj æj lævardtoncæ lægmæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>против желания выдавали ее замуж</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>she was married against her desire</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>I 55</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Из %ifænd%i + %ion%i. Образование имеет характер отглагольного, а не отыменного (ср. употребление суффикса %i-on%i в %ikænon%i ‘поведение’ от <xr><ref target="#entry_kænyn"/></xr>, %iwarzon%i ‘любимый’ от <xr><ref target="#entry_warzyn"/></xr>, %iiw-daron%i ‘будничный’ от <xr><ref target="#entry_daryn"/></xr> и др.). Поэтому и в %ifændon%i правильнее видеть дериват от глагола %ifændyn%i | %ifændun%i ‘желать’, а не от %ifænd%i ‘намерение’ и пр. См. <xr><ref target="#entry_fændyn"/><ref target="#entry_fænd"/></xr>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From %ifænd%i + %ion%i. It is a deverbal derivative, not denominal one (cf. the use of the suffix %i-on%i in %ikænon%i ‘behaviour’ from <xr><ref target="#entry_kænyn"/></xr>, %iwarzon%i ‘favourite’ from <xr><ref target="#entry_warzyn"/></xr>, %iiw-daron%i ‘everyday’ from <xr><ref target="#entry_daryn"/></xr> etc.). That is why it is more correct to view %ifændon%i as a derivative from the verb %ifændyn%i | %ifændun%i ‘wish’, not from the word %ifænd%i ‘intention’ etc. See <xr><ref target="#entry_fændyn"/><ref target="#entry_fænd"/></xr>.</etym></entry>